.org/index.php?realm=more&amp;gototype=modern&amp;type=essay&amp;book=essay9">"Peter Nockles, \'\'The Nineteenth Century Reception\'\', Acts and Monuments online"</a>. Johnfoxe.org<span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">2013-04-16</span></span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AFoxe%27s+Book+of+Martyrs&amp;rft.btitle=Peter+Nockles%2C+%27%26%2339%3BThe+Nineteenth+Century+Reception%27%26%2339%3B%2C+Acts+and+Monuments+online&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.pub=Johnfoxe.org&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.johnfoxe.org%2Findex.php%3Frealm%3Dmore%26gototype%3Dmodern%26type%3Dessay%26book%3Dessay9&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-55"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-55">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Jose Harris, <i>Private Lives, Public Spirit: a Social History of Britain, 1870-1914</i> (London: Penguin, 1994)</span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-56"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-56">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">D. Trenow, "The Credibility of John Foxe, the \'martyrologist\' (1868), quoted in Freeman, <i>ODNB</i>.</span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-57"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-57">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">pending</span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-58"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-58">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.hrionline.ac.uk/johnfoxe/index.html"><i>Foxe\'s Book of Martyrs Variorum Edition</i></a>. In 2010, the project entered "Phase 2".</span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-59"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-59">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Warren Wooden, <i>John Foxe</i> (Twayne, 1983), 110.</span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-60"><span class="mw-cite-back